channel.title: My compiler?
channel.description:
I had the javac error in my compiler so i followed lots of tutorials to get it fixed WHICH I DID. It compiles perfectly apart from when it compiles the server, the server doesnt change what i changed. E.g: I change a send message from "hello" to "bye", it was stay as "hello". Can anybody help?
Thanks.

item.title: My compiler?
item.dc:creator: @Gh0stb4rr4g3 Gh0stb4rr4g3
item.description:
@Gh0stb4rr4g3 wrote:

Right click on it , edit.
Look at the java version , change it 2 urs.

Change something in client.java , save it.
After that compile (Server must be down at this part)

After compiling it , run the server. (Only if u get 0 errors.)

It should work then. If not send me the code of ur compiler.

-gh0st
